# Copy to .env for reference. The simulator has no database (in-memory by design).
#
# Control plane (POST /reset, /play-next, /run) is identity-based: it requires a
# Bearer token whose `admin` claim is true (the shared AdminGuard reads it). No
# shared admin keys, no x-admin-key headers — authority is carried in the token.
# Reads (/state, /health) stay open to any valid token (/health is public).
#
# Shared JWT secret (@arena/service-auth): verifies inbound Bearer tokens and
# signs the simulator's own admin service tokens for pricing/betting calls. Must
# match the other services' SESSION_SECRET; unset locally = the shared dev fallback.
# SESSION_SECRET="<shared-session-secret>"

# Where the finale chain and the reset cascade fan out. Unset locally = the
# @arena/contracts BASE_URLS localhost defaults; deploys point these at the live
# services.
# PRICING_URL="https://pricing.example.com"
# BETTING_URL="https://betting.example.com"

# Optional: fix the RNG seed for a reproducible tournament (unset = different
# every run).
# SIM_SEED=20260703
